s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:32:\"http://webdevstudios.com/?p=8852\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:730:\"<p>Recently Chris Reynolds brought up an issue he was experiencing with one of our client projects; he was struggling to compare the current active status for plugins in a multisite network between internal dev servers and a WPEngine staging site so that he could debug ... <a class=\"moretag button orange\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/2015/01/22/checking-plugin-activation-status-on-wordpress-multisite-networks/\">Read More</a></p>
